</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,259,285]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Remarks</emphasis>
. Only 
<specimenCount box="[385,511,259,285]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
specimens have been recorded for this species and the male is still unknown (Shinohara 1995). No molecular data are available. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[687,897,295,321]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
placed this species in his 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gussakovskij" authorityYear="1935" box="[1190,1324,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictifrons">
<emphasis box="[1190,1324,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">P. pictifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1812" box="[223,325,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrio">
<emphasis box="[223,325,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">P. histrio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N." box="[413,609,331,357]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="20 - 117" refId="ref79858" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. (2017) Suborder Symphyta - Sawflies and wood wasps. In: Lelej, A. S., Proshchalykin, M. Yu. &amp; Loktionov, V. M. (Eds.), Annotated catalogue of the Hymenoptera of Russia. Vol. I. Symphyta and Apocrita: Aculeata. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, Supplement 6, pp. 20 - 117." type="journal article" year="2017">Sundukov (2017)</bibRefCitation>
noted “Host plant:? 
<taxonomicName box="[845,955,331,357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[845,901,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Rosa</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[971,1082,331,357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
)” but this host record, which is probably based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Verzhutskij, B. N." box="[363,575,367,393]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 303" refId="ref80536" refString="Verzhutskij, B. N. (1981) Rastitel'nojadnye nasekomye v ekosistemakh Vostochnoj Sibiri (pilil'shchiki i rogokhvosty). Nauka, Novosibirsk, pp. 1 - 303." type="book chapter" year="1981">Verzhutskij (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, is doubtful as discussed by Shinohara (1995).
</paragraph>
